foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Column one should be the same number as the number of pending FOIA requests reported byeach component at the end of FY09. The differences in numbers for AF, DISA, DODIG, JFCOM, NAVY, NORTHCOM, NSA, OSD/JS, PACOM, SOCOM, and STRATCOM are due to better accounting methods which caused some minor discrepancy in starting numbers. The numbers for OSD/JS are also different because some cases reported as "pending FOIA requests" at the end of FY09 wer re-classified as consultations.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: Concerning all tables in Section VI, not all components process administrative appeals. OSD/JS FOIA Appeals Branch processes the following components’ appeals: AFRICOM, CENTCOM, DoDEA, DTIC, EUCOM, JFCOM, NGB, NORTHCOM, OSD/JS, PACOM, SOCOM, SOUTHCOM, STRATCOM, TRANSCOM, and TRICARE.

Column one should be the same number as the number of pending FOIA requests reported by each component at the end of FY09. The differences in numbers for AF, DIA DoD IG and OSD/JS are due to better accounting methods which caused some minor discrepancy in starting numbers.

foia:AppealDispositionSection.foia:FootnoteText: ABSCA, DeCA and DSS did not process any appeals in FY10.

foia:AppealResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD (Agency) medians. Furthermore, Army has multiple reporting components and is not able to compute medians for its overall totals.
ABSCA, DeCA and DSS did not process any appeals in FY10.

foia:ProcessedResponseTimeSection.foia:FootnoteText: Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD (Agency) medians. Furthermore, Army has multiple reporting components and was not able to compute medians for its overall totals. This applies to all tables with medians in Section VII.

foia:ComplexResponseTimeIncrementsSectio.foia:FootnoteText: There was no area above to report the number of cases processed in less than a day. Therefore, we combined these numbers within the "1-20 day category. The instances in which DoD components closed cases in less than one day is provided as follows: AF - 42; Army - 130; DLA - 104; DoDIG - 34; DTRA - 3; Navy - 321; OSD/JS - 3; SOCOM - 4; TRICARE - 1. The actual instances in which DoD Components closed cases 1-20 days is provided as follows: AF - 508; Army - 9410; CENTCOM - 5; DCAA - 1; DFAS - 24; DISA - 90; DLA - 200; DoD IG - 166; DTRA - 78; JFCOM - 2; Navy - 893; NGA - 1; NGB - 9; OSD/JS - 148; PACOM - 15; SOCOM - 33; TRICARE - 25

foia:ExpeditedProcessingSection.foia:FootnoteText: If the component has neither granted nor denied expedited processing then the third, fourth and fifth columns are designated N/A.

foia:FeeWaiverSection.foia:FootnoteText: If the component has neither granted nor denied fee waivers the third and fourth column is designated as N/A

Due to the decentralized processing and tracking of FOIA requests within the DoD and because the DoD does not have the means to centrally capture all the required data, it is not possible to calculate DoD medians and the medians for some components that have more than one FOIA requester service center.

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: Not all components process administrative appeals. OSD/JS FOIA Appeals Branch processes the following components’ appeals: AFRICOM, CENTCOM, DoDEA, DTIC, EUCOM, JFCOM, NGB, NORTHCOM, PACOM, SOCOM, SOUTHCOM, TRANSCOM, and TRICARE.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: The numbers in this column should equal the numbers reported in the previous year’s report. The numbers for OSD/JS and SOCOM are also different because some cases reported as “pending FOIA requests” at the end of FY09 were re-classified as consultations.
